# Class: :BWMD_0010447 (Material Batch)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label :BWMD_0010447 "Material Batch"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(owl:versionInfo :BWMD_0010447 "This class was added by Elena Garcia Trelles (Fraunhofer IWM)")
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition :BWMD_0010447 "A set of material objects which share a common manufacturing history and therefore share similar mechanical properties. For example, one specific material batch is typically defined by its manufacturing process and subsequent heat treatment steps. A material batch is identified by its own tracking number or \"MaterialBatchID\"."@en)
SubClassOf(:BWMD_0010447 :BWMD_0010051)

# Class: :BWMD_0010448 (Material Batch ID)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label :BWMD_0010448 "Material Batch ID"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(owl:versionInfo :BWMD_0010448 "This class was added by Elena Garcia Trelles (Fraunhofer IWM)")
AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition :BWMD_0010448 "concept to express a particular state of a material after defined by a particular history which has to some extend affected the material mechanical properties, e.g. the hardness characteristic values, the yield stress, the fatigue lifetime, etc. 
In many material science projects, different batches of a material are characterized by small changes in composition or heat treatment history. Each particular batch gets its own identifier and this is the role of the \"MaterialBatchID\"."@en)
SubClassOf(:BWMD_0010448 :BWMD_0010537)

