AnnotationAssertion(skos:definition :BWMD_0010831 "The thermal expansion coefficient, often denoted as α, is a temperature dependent material property that quantifies the amount a material expands or contracts in response to a change in temperature. It is typically expressed as the fractional change in length (or volume) per degree change in temperature."@en)
